\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 8. I. spuria} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 39 (1753). Stems 30-90 cm, bearing several leaves. Basal leaves 25-90 cm × 6-20 mm, somewhat fetid. Flowers (1-)2-4; pedicels 5-20 mm; spathes 40-80(-120) mm, herbaceous, but often with membranous apex or margins. Hypanthial tube 7-10 mm, campanulate; sterile beak of ovary up to 40 mm. Falls 30-80 × 10-30 mm; limb elliptical to orbicular, shorter than the claw. Standards 30-60 × 8-20 mm, narrowly obovate. Capsule 2·5-4 cm (excluding beak), with 6 conspicuous longitudinal ridges. Seeds angular, brown, with loose, membranous testa.{\i  Wet places, on calcareous or saline soils. From S. Sweden to C. Spain, N.E. Greece and S. Ukraine.} Au *Br Cz Da Ga Ge Gr Hs Hu Rm Rs (W) Su [It].
