\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b a}) Subsp. {\b spuria}: Stems (50-)60-80 cm. Basal leaves 8-12 mm wide. Upper cauline leaves shorter than internodes. Spathes membranous at apex. Falls 45-60 mm, lilac, with violet veins and yellow central stripe. 2n = 22. •{\i  C. Europe, extending to S. Sweden and} ({\i doubtfully native}) {\i E. England}.
