\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b b}) Subsp. {\b maritima} P. Fourn., {\i Quatre Fl. Fr.} 190 (1935) ({\i I. maritima} Lam., non Miller): Stems 30-40(-50) cm. Basal leaves 6-8(-10) mm wide. Upper cauline leaves longer than internodes. Spathes entirely herbaceous. Falls 30-45 mm, cream, with violet-blue veins.{\i  S.W. Europe}.
\par

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b c}) Subsp. {\b balophila} (Pallas) D.A. Webb & Chater,{\i  Bot. Jour. Linn. Soc.}{\b  76}: 315 (1978) ({\i I. halophila} Pallas): Stems 40-90 cm. Basal leaves 7-12 mm wide. Upper cauline leaves longer than internodes. Spathes with membranous apex and margins. Falls 40-60 mm, pale yellow with deeper veins, patent. 2n = 20.{\i  From S. Romania to E. Ukraine}.
\par

