\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 10. I. sintenisii} Janka, {\i Term. Füz. }{\b 1}: 244 (1877). Like {\b 9} but stems cylindrical or slightly compressed, not winged; basal leaves 20-50 cm × 1·5-5 mm; spathes 40-70 mm, all alike, keeled; falls 8-12 mm wide; flowers violet-blue, not fragrant; sterile upper portion of ovary 12-22 mm, very slender.{\i  S.E. Europe, from S. Albania to Moldavia; S. Italy.} Al Bu Gr It Ju Rm Rs (W) Tu.
